  faqs={[
    { question: "How do I check my MEPCO bill online in March 2026?", answer: "Enter your 14-digit MEPCO reference number in the bill checker at the top of this page and click Check Bill. Your complete MEPCO electricity bill for March 2026 appears on screen in seconds — showing amount due, due date, units consumed, meter readings, and all charges. This is completely free, needs no login, and works 24 hours a day, 7 days a week." },
    { question: "Where is my MEPCO 14-digit reference number on the bill?", answer: "Your MEPCO reference number is printed in bold at the top of your electricity bill — usually on the upper-right area of the page near your consumer name and address. It is also printed on the tear-off payment stub at the bottom. It is always 14 digits long. Save it in your phone — this number never changes for your connection." },
    { question: "How do I check my MEPCO bill by SMS?", answer: "Type pitc followed by a space and your 14-digit MEPCO reference number, then send to 8334. For example: pitc 12345678901234. You receive your current bill amount, due date, and units consumed as an SMS reply within seconds. Standard SMS charges apply from your mobile operator." },
    { question: "Can I check MEPCO bill by Consumer ID?", answer: "Yes. Click the Customer ID tab in the bill checker above and enter your 10-digit Consumer ID. Your MEPCO Consumer ID is printed below your name on the bill, labeled Consumer No. or Account No. Both the reference number and Consumer ID pull the exact same complete bill from the PITC server." },
    { question: "How do I download my MEPCO duplicate bill as PDF?", answer: "After your MEPCO bill loads on screen, click the Download PDF button. Your browser opens the print dialog — select Save as PDF as your printer destination and click Save. Your MEPCO duplicate bill downloads instantly as a PDF file. You can then share it on WhatsApp, email it, or print it at any nearby printing shop for payment." },
    { question: "Why is my MEPCO bill very high this month?", answer: "Common reasons for a high MEPCO bill: (1) AC usage in South Punjab summers — temperatures above 45°C in Multan and DG Khan force ACs to run 16+ hours daily; (2) High FPA (Fuel Price Adjustment) set by NEPRA for this billing month; (3) You crossed from Protected to Unprotected status due to 6-month average exceeding 200 units; (4) Estimated bill from previous months combined with current actual; (5) Meter reading error — check if the bill says Estimated instead of Actual." },
    { question: "What are MEPCO's peak hours?", answer: "MEPCO summer peak hours (April to October) are 6:30 PM to 10:30 PM. Winter peak hours (November to March) are 6:00 PM to 10:00 PM. Running heavy appliances — AC, washing machine, iron, electric geyser — during these windows costs more per unit for connections with sanctioned load above 5kW. Shifting these appliances to before 6 PM or after 11 PM saves most MEPCO households Rs 200–500 per month." },
    { question: "How do I pay my MEPCO bill online?", answer: "Pay through JazzCash, Easypaisa, or any bank mobile app. Open the app, go to Bill Payments, select Electricity, choose MEPCO or WAPDA, enter your 14-digit reference number, verify the amount shown, and confirm payment. You receive an instant SMS confirmation with a transaction ID. Online payment posts to MEPCO's system within 2 to 4 hours." },
    { question: "What is the MEPCO bill grace period?", answer: "MEPCO gives 7 days after the due date printed on the bill to pay without a late payment surcharge. After the grace period ends, a 10% surcharge applies to the entire unpaid amount. On a Rs 8,000 MEPCO bill, paying even one day after the grace period costs you an extra Rs 800. Always pay on or before your due date." },
    { question: "How do I check MEPCO load shedding schedule for my area?", answer: "Visit ccms.pitc.com.pk and enter your 14-digit MEPCO reference number. Click Search. Your specific feeder's complete load shedding schedule appears — showing which hours each day your area has no electricity. MEPCO implements feeder-wise load shedding. Areas with higher bill recovery rates receive less load shedding under MEPCO policy." },
    { question: "Which districts does MEPCO cover?", answer: "MEPCO covers 13 districts of South Punjab: Multan, Bahawalpur, Rahim Yar Khan, Dera Ghazi Khan, Sahiwal, Pakpattan, Khanewal, Lodhran, Vehari, Muzaffargarh, Bahawalnagar, Layyah, and Bhakkar. MEPCO is Pakistan's largest DISCO by geographic coverage, serving one of the country's most agriculturally productive regions." },
    { question: "How do I file a billing complaint with MEPCO?", answer: "Call MEPCO helpline 118 or 0800-63726 with your reference number ready. Describe the billing issue — overbilling, wrong category, TP penalty, or incorrect reading — and note down the Complaint Registration Number (CRN) the agent gives you. If MEPCO does not resolve within 14 working days, escalate to NEPRA at 0800-63000 (toll-free). NEPRA decisions are legally binding on MEPCO." },
  ]}

